      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        If a Register is closed, "X [ ]" is added to string s. If a Register is open and has no Customers, " [ ]" is added to string s. If a Register is open and has Customers, " [n]x" is added to string s (where "n" represents the amount of groceries a Customer has, and "x" represents the amount of Customer(s) in the Queue, which are represented by the character "@").
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        string The finished string s.
